        "possibleIdentity": "Maxwell R. Rimler was a civil and structural engineer active in the late 1960s and early 1970s. He graduated from Columbia University in 1948 with a degree in Civil Engineering ('48CE). Born in the early 1920s, he attended Miami Beach High School (Class of 1941), where he expressed an ambition to become an aeronautical engineer. His professional expertise included structural engineering with a focus on modern materials such as fiberglass, plastics/polymers, acrylics, and foam, as well as industrial design. Based in East Meadow, New York, he was associated with the non-profit organization Experiments in Art and Technology (E.A.T.), which facilitated collaborations between members of the technical community and artists.",
